1.00	Tunes_of_glory	Tunes of Glory	Tunes of Glory is a 1960 British film directed by Ronald Neame, based on the novel and screenplay by James Kennaway. The film is a "dark psychological drama" centring on events in a Scottish Highland regimental barracks in the period following World War II. It stars Alec Guinness and John Mills, and features Dennis Price, Kay Walsh, John Fraser, Susannah York, Duncan MacRae and Gordon Jackson.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7a/Tunes_of_glory76.jpg/225px-Tunes_of_glory76.jpg
